summary: Completed comprehensive testing of My Coach Developer iPad coach observation app including backend API testing and frontend integration testing. All major features and recent bug fixes are working correctly including ball rolling state persistence, AI summary generation, PDF/CSV export, session notes, and editable templates.
passed_tests: Backend API: Root endpoint returns 'Hello World' (200 OK)
Backend API: Status check creation and retrieval working
Backend API: AI summary generation with realistic coaching data (2737 chars generated)
Backend API: AI summary handles empty data gracefully
Backend API: Proper validation errors for missing fields (422 status)
Frontend: Home page loads correctly with 'My Coach Developer' title
Frontend: Create new session navigation works
Frontend: Default session parts correctly renamed to 'Part 1', 'Part 2', 'Part 3', 'Part 4'
Frontend: Live observation page loads with 3-column grid layout
Frontend: Ball rolling toggle works (changes from 'Ball Not Rolling' to 'Ball Rolling')
Frontend: Ball rolling state persists when switching between session parts (bug fix verified)
Frontend: Can add new parts during live session (Part 5 added successfully)
Frontend: Session timer starts and runs correctly
Frontend: Event logging works (Command, Q&A events logged)
Frontend: Descriptor selection works after event logging
Frontend: Session completion navigates to review page
Frontend: Notes & AI tab exists and is accessible
Frontend: Session notes can be saved successfully
Frontend: AI summary generation works and integrates with backend API
Frontend: PDF export button works (clicked successfully)
Frontend: CSV export button works (clicked successfully)
Frontend: Templates page loads and displays templates
Frontend: Template expansion/editing works (events, descriptors, parts editable)
Frontend: New template creation works
Frontend: Session parts in templates show correct Part 1-4 naming
